{
  "texts": [
    "These different mechanisms of action have related but distinct networks.",
    "Within this 129-edge subnetwork, 19% of edges are predictable by Model L alone.",
    "19% of the predicted edges are either \"known\" or \"pIC 50 \" and 54% are supported by pQSAR evidence, implying high predictive quality.",
    "Among all the network edges, 2183 (1.5%) are supported by all three models: Model L, Model pQSAR, and the combined model.",
    "Furthermore, 4566 (3.1%) edges found support in orthogonal data sources (not counting pQSAR), including 113 by NCI 60, 58 by PSP, 502 by structure similarity, 1271 by experimental pIC 50 data, and 2622 are \"known\" interactions."
  ]
}